This paper deals with the task of human parsing, which involves decomposing a human image into semantic fashion/body regions. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) as it requires the use of deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) to build an end-to-end relation between the input image and the structure outputs for human parsing. Additionally, the paper involves image processing techniques such as super-pixel smoothing, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed method, which involves comparing it to other state-of-the-art algorithms, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
